Epidemic of cholera in the north of Cameroon: 10 deaths
--------------------------------------------------------
According to a report on Sat 12 Sep 1998, about 10 people have died in a
few days in a cholera epidemic in the north of Cameroon, since the rains
started a month ago.
According to the health authorities in Garoua, capital of Northern
Province, a hundred or so cases have been registered and new cases are
appearing daily.
Medical students are forming volunteer teams to care for the population and
provide advice.
